    comment = {Examines evidence for speech perception having either specialized or general mechanisms, in particular in the context of pitch perception but to throw light on more general question.

Domain specificity comes from motor theory, which describes a 'special' speech processing module.  On the other side is cue specificity, which says special modules are unneccesary.  Both have some experimental support, which researchers may pick and choose to support their POV...  However reviewed evidence shows a strong form of either is untenable.

